Detailed Description

Structure for allowed values of content type properties and parameters. Use one of val_enum or data_type, size, and display_name

Field Documentation

const CHAR* SyncMLCTValueDef::m_data_type
 

Specifies the type of a supported content type. Corresponds to the DataType element in the SyncML Device Information DTD.

const CHAR* SyncMLCTValueDef::m_display_name
 

Specifies the display name of the given content type property or parameter. Corresponds to the DisplayName element in the SyncML Device Information DTD.

UINT32 SyncMLCTValueDef::m_size
 

Specifies the size of a property or a parameter of a given content type. Corresponds to the Size element in the SyncML Device Information DTD.

const CHAR* SyncMLCTValueDef::m_val_enum
 

Specifies the supported enumerated value of a given content type property. Corresponds to the ValEnum element in the SyncML Device Information DTD.
